Earlier this week, The Guardian reported that U.S. President Donald Trump offered CureVac “large sums of money” for exclusive access to the Covid-19 vaccine, which the German government protested.
On March 17, 2020, the American pharmaceutical company Pfizer announced a partnership with the German company BioNTech to jointly develop a vaccine based on mRNA.
