In China, about 30% of people hospitalized with COVID-19 end up in intensive care.
The task of providing artificial lung ventilation is complicated as acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) developing in COVID-19 and oxygenation are causing more and more problems.
Inhaled pressure ventilators and ventilators are needed to deliver the maximum amount of oxygen to the lungs and to ensure minimal ventilation damage, which can lead to the development of pneumothorax.
